Come have an old fashioned with me!
There is nothing like good strong cup of sweet tea and a scone to warm you up on a blustery day.  I got a pretty substantial beard trim too😃

Mom and I went for breakfast at @10.cows.creamery this morning and I bought this little cake from their bakery.
It makes a nice second breakfast 😋 We really enjoyed ourselves. It is a very nice place.

Midnight is a good companion on a car ride. Dad, Mom and I  went for a ride to Savage River State Park. We went for a short walk, but I bet it would be fun to explore some of the hiking trails. There were a few signs of spring, is winter officially over?

My Mother made this counted cross stitch floral scarf. I found it when I was snooping through the linen drawer of her china closet.
I am very impressed!
 I know I am drinking tea from a coffee cup but I really like is so I am throwing propriety, decorum and etiquette to the wind....
Micah is growing up so fast!
The kids had a fun day playing and riding bikes. They even found a blackberry patch! I am so thankful they send me so many pictures.
Good morning from Mister Jynx! 🐈‍⬛🌞🌻
I am having a nice healthy tomato juice while I wait for my flight....
I am having breakfast on top of the world!
Micah and his Aunt Heaven need a break from swimming! I wish I was there too!❤
Zamira is contemplating her life choices.....
Mister Jynx is glad that I am home!
Heaven and I are enjoying a nice French breakfast here in Brooklyn.
We had a fun time touring NYC today!
I went to The Back Room tonight. It is an authentic prohibition era speakeasy, they serve the cocktails in tea cups!
My daughter took this picture of a squirrel eating a mushroom outside of her apartment.
I am making a valance for a friend. She sent me a picture, the picture only had one row of granny squares, I think 2 rows is much nicer. I will arrange these like a checker board.
Princessita is Zamira chasing bubbles!
Good afternoon from Mister Jynx

I tested positive for covid last Friday and have been
convalescing in bed for over a week. Yesterday, I still tested positive. I am not feeling so bad now, but the symptoms are really lingering.  This is my covid recovery sweater. Why not take advantage of this time to make myself something special? The Yarn is 100% American grown and processed. It is called Local Grown by Lion Brand Yarn.
